{
  "texts": [
    "This approach can enhance theory development in two ways.",
    "Firstly, it can enable the researcher to theorize about potential underlying causal mechanisms by tweaking micro-level aspects of a complex system (Davis et al., 2007).",
    "This is especially true if one takes advantage of LLMs' language generation capabilities and solicits rationales for their decisions, which can help to make sense of the observed behavior.",
    "4 The other benefit of this approach is that it can provide a clearer impression of boundary conditions for models that cannot be solved in a closed form.",
    "Articulating all the relevant assumptions and then relaxing them in the simulations can help to both generalize and bound theories (Makadok et al., 2018)."
  ]
}